<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 6: The Mystery File</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>🔮 Challenge 6: The Mystery File</h1>
      <p class="desc">This file says it's a <code>.dat</code> — but it's lying about its identity. Unmask it!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="story-box">
        A suspicious file called <code>mystery_file.dat</code> was found on a hacked computer. Here's the thing — <strong>file extensions can be faked!</strong> Every file type has a secret fingerprint in its first few bytes called a "magic number." Find the file's true identity, open it the right way, and the flag is yours.
      </div>

      <a href="/challenge/6/download" class="download-btn">📥 Download Mystery File</a>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠️ How to unmask a file</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Open it in a text editor (Notepad) and look at the very first characters</li>
          <li>Common fingerprints: <code>%PDF</code> = PDF, <code>PK</code> = ZIP, <code>89 PNG</code> = PNG</li>
          <li>Once you know the real type, rename the extension and open it!</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Hint 1</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Open the file in Notepad or any text editor. What do the first few characters say?</p>
        </details>
        <details style="margin-top: 10px;">
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Hint 2</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">It starts with <code>%PDF</code> — rename <code>.dat</code> to <code>.pdf</code> and open it!</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch6')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
